Fargo.KVOX-FM:
KVOX-FM (99.9 FM, "Froggy 99.9") is a country radio station located in Fargo, North Dakota (licensed by the Federal Communications Commission (FCC) to twin city Moorhead, Minnesota), owned by Duey Wright's Midwest Communications, Inc.


== History ==
KVOX-FM first aired in 1978, branding themselves as "Stereo Country K100". This would remain as their branding until April 1, 1994 when they officially released "on-air", the "Froggy" Moniker which is still used to this day.
